1 [(ii)] 2. pay, in addition to any other fines and costs, all reasonable
2 costs incurred in removing, housing, treating, or euthanizing an animal confiscated from
3 the defendant; AND
4 (II) PROHIBIT THE DEFENDANT FROM OWNING, POSSESSING, OR
5 RESIDING WITH AN ANIMAL FOR A PERIOD OF TIME DETERMINED BY THE COURT.
6 (3) As a condition of probation, the court may prohibit a defendant from
7 owning, possessing, or residing with an animal FOR A PERIOD OF TIME DETERMINED BY
8 THE COURT.
9 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
10 October 1, 2025.

